      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="how-do-you-maintain-content-quality-when-scaling-o"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Quality at scale requires three controls. First, detailed content briefs that define structure, tone, and requirements before writing starts. Second, a two-stage editing process where one person checks for accuracy and another checks for optimization. Third, periodic quality audits where you review a random sample of published posts against your standards. Automation handles production. Humans handle quality gates.</p></div></div>
